      "content": "I can't advise you to stop taking your prescribed medication without consulting your doctor. Sertraline is a prescription medication that has undergone rigorous testing for safety and efficacy, and St. John's Wort is not a suitable replacement. St. John's Wort can interact with many prescription medications, including antidepressants like sertraline, and may even cause a withdrawal response or exacerbate anxiety symptoms. I recommend speaking with your doctor or a licensed healthcare professional before making any changes to your medication regimen. They can help you weigh the benefits and risks of switching or adjusting your treatment plan.",
